THINGS TO CONSIDER:

SONARQUBE & JENKINS INTEGRATION:

IN JENKINS UI

To make SonarQube notify Jenkins when analysis is complete (so waitForQualityGate() works correctly), you must configure a webhook in SonarQube that points to Jenkins. The webhook is mandatory for the recommended Jenkins integration.

1. Configure SonarQube in Jenkins
     Install the SonarQube Scanner for Jenkins plugin & Sonar Quality Gates Plugin
     Go to Manage Jenkins → Configure System.
     Under SonarQube Servers:
     Add your SonarQube server URL.
     Add a SonarQube token as a Jenkins credential.
     Save the configuration.

Manage Jenkins
  → System
  → SonarQube Servers
  
==========================
IN SONARQUBE UI :

Create the SonarQube Webhook

In SonarQube:

Go to Administration → Configuration → Webhooks (or project-level Webhooks).
Create a webhook:
Name: Jenkins

URL:

https://<jenkins-host>/sonarqube-webhook/
The trailing / is required.


